# PayrunJob Import Integration Test
# Tests POST /api/tenants/{tenantId}/payruns/jobs/import
#
# Test scenario:
#   1. Set up tenant with 2 completed payrun jobs (Jan/Feb 2024)
#   2. Export payrun jobs via GET (→ Export.PayrunJobs.json)
#   3. Export payroll result sets via GET (→ Export.ResultSets.json)
#   4. DELETE all payrun jobs (simulates archiving — removes jobs + results)
#   5. Import via POST /payruns/jobs/import using a pre-composed PayrunJobSet file
#   6. Verify payrun jobs are present after import
#
# Note: The import endpoint expects PayrunJobSet[] (job + resultSets combined).
# Composing Export.PayrunJobs.json + Export.ResultSets.json into Import.PayrunJobSets.json
# must be done by a client service outside this script — see PayrollArchiving-Concept.md.
#
# URL placeholders:
#   {tenant:PayrunJobImport.Test} → resolved to numeric tenant id at runtime

Delete.pecmd
PayrunTest Test.pt.json /keeptest

# --- Export payrun jobs from Primary-DB ---
HttpGet api/tenants/{tenant:PayrunJobImport.Test}/payruns/jobs Export.PayrunJobs.json

# --- Export payroll result sets from Primary-DB ---
HttpGet api/tenants/{tenant:PayrunJobImport.Test}/payrollresults/sets Export.ResultSets.json

# --- Simulate archive: delete all payrun jobs (cascades to results) ---
PayrunJobDelete PayrunJobImport.Test

# --- Import payrun job sets back into Primary-DB ---
# Prerequisite: Import.PayrunJobSets.json must be composed client-side
# from Export.PayrunJobs.json + Export.ResultSets.json before running this step.
# Expected return value: 2 (Jan24 + Feb24)
HttpPost api/tenants/{tenant:PayrunJobImport.Test}/payruns/jobs/import Import.PayrunJobSets.json

# --- Verify payrun jobs are present after import ---
HttpGet api/tenants/{tenant:PayrunJobImport.Test}/payruns/jobs Verify.PayrunJobs.json

Delete.pecmd
